channel switch, make history\nloading robust with try/finally and polling, broaden IRC nick prefix\nstripping to @+%~&, handle unhandled promise rejection when sending\ntyping events, add a copilot review checklist, and make\nserialize-on-error safer in server working_files. These changes fix\ncorrectness and robustness problems uncovered during review (race\nconditions, unre\n[TRUNCATED]\ntyping indicators originating from history\n\nTyping indicator events from message history can be stale and cause\nincorrect \"user is typing\" displays for offline users. Add a batch field\nto the typing message type and silently ignore Typing events that\nreference a known history batch so that historical typing markers are\nnot shown as live indicators.\nSeparate server and SASL passwords for IRC\n\nSplit the single IRC password field into two distinct configurable\nfields: a shared server_password (sent as PASS to gate the connection)\nand a per-user sasl_password (used for SASL PLAIN authentication and\nregistered on first use). This updates UI labels/placeholders, settings\nAPIs, config structs, lifecycle/manager/manager tests, and client logic\nto handle both passwords correctly, ensure TLS is enforced when any\npassword is set, and avoid sending PASS when SASL handled auth. The\nchange clarifies purpose of each password and preserves behavior for\nempty/whitespace values.\nDocument plaintext storage for IRC passwords\n\nMake it explicit in the UI and settings that IRC server and SASL\npasswords are stored in plaintext and should not be real or reused\npasswords. Added explanatory captions in the IRC settings UI and\nsecurity notes in the app settings comments, and adjusted tests/config\ndefaults to avoid carrying a real password value. This clarifies the\nsecurity posture and guides users to use low-value shared secrets\ninstead of personal credentials.\nRequire both IRC passwords before connecting\n\nAvoid attempting to establish IRC connections unless both the server\npassword and the SASL/account password are present and non-empty. The\nchange centralizes trimming/empty checks and returns None (skipping the\nconnection) with debug logs if either password is missing. Tests and\nexamples were updated to reflect the new requirement: doc/example values\nrenamed, helper constructors added for connections with passwords, and\ntests adjusted to assert None when passwords are missing and to verify\nboth passwords are preserved when present.\n","tool_name":"exec_command","tool_kind":"exec","tool_input":null,"exit_code":0,"outcome":"succeeded","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-26T11:47:24.939Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}